0in%20other%20sectors%E2%80%9D.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20think%20that%20he%20has%20a%20point%20here%20when%20he%20says%20that%20there%20is%20overall%20positive%20sentiment%20about%20India.%20Some%20of%20it%20is%20because%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20great%20ability%20at%20public%20relations%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20working%20well%20for%20India.%20But%20some%20of%20it%20also%20is%20because%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20is%20the%20China%2B1%20strategy.%20People%20are%20looking%20for%20alternatives%20to%20China.%20We%20aren%E2%80%99t%20capturing%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20business.%20Vietnam%20is%20capturing%20more.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20another%20reason%20people%20are%20looking%20at%20us.%20But%20a%20manufacturer%20like%20Apple%20or%20anybody%20serious%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20go%20based%20on%20headlines.%20It%20looks%20at%20ground%20realities.%20How%20easy%20is%20it%20to%20do%20business%20here%3F%20Should%20I%20come%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20reality%20is%20it%20still%20is%20quite%20hard%20to%20do%20business%20in%20India.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20talked%20to%20sort%20of%20potential%20FDI%20people%20here%2C%20they%20really%20are%20still%20worried%20about%20all%20those%20impediments.%20And%20if%20you%20look%20at%20FDI%20into%20India%2C%20look%20at%20World%20Bank%20numbers%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20stuck%20at%201.5%25%20of%20GDP%20for%20the%20last%20so%20many%20years.%20So%20really%2C%20I%20mean%20it%E2%80%99s%20you%20know%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20data%20closely%20%E2%80%93%20all%20this%20%E2%80%98India%20Shining%E2%80%99%20and%20everything%20is%20coming%20in%20and%20wonderful%20and%20so%20%E2%80%93%20the%20bare%20data%20says%20we%20have%20to%20do%20a%20little%20more.%20I%E2%80%99m%20hopeful.%20I%20think%20India%20is%20capable%20of%20a%20lot.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20first%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20sort%20of%20perception%20management%20and%20look%20at%20the%20details.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20not%20fool%20ourselves%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20worst%20way%20to%20go.%20Eventually%2C%20people%20find%20out%20the%20truth%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20problem.%20So%20unless%20we%E2%80%99re%20fixing%20those%20disabilities%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20going%20to%20have%20a%20big%20role%20in%20manufacturing%2C%20but%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20on%20it%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20going%20to%20say%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20jobs%20are%2C%20and%20when%20the%20jobs%20don%E2%80%99t%20come%20you%20can%20see%20the%20frustration%20spilling%20out%20in%20places%20like%20Manipur.%20Where%20you%20know%20it%20all%20it%20started%20with%20as%20you%20remember%20reservations.%20Because%20everybody%E2%80%99s%20looking%20for%20reservations%20given%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20find%20good%20private%20sector%20jobs.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20get%20reservation%20in%20government%20jobs%2C%20for%20example%2C%20because%20that%20is%20our%20ticket%20to%20a%20middle-class%20life.%20Those%20forces%20are%20going%20to%20increase%20tremendously%20unless%20we%20do%20something%20about%20it%2C%20and%20that%20means%20real%20jobs%20and%20not%2C%20you%20know%20well..%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20Rs%203.2%20crore%20jobs%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20those%20were%20worth%20Rs%203.2%20crore%2C%20even%20that%20may%20be%20okay.%20But%20Rs%203.2%20crore%20per%20moderately%20skilled%20job%20is%20too%20much.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20finally%2C%20above%20and%20beyond%20his%20criticisms%20of%20your%20analysis%2C%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%20has%20also%20attacked%20you%20in%20personal%20terms.%20He%E2%80%99s%20accused%20you%20of%20lacking%20pride%2C%20self-respect%2C%20and%20even%20dignity%2C%20of%20bankruptcy%20of%20morals%2C%20and%20believe%20it%20or%20not%20of%20an%20over-simplistic%20mind.%20Do%20you%20really%20want%20to%20respond%20to%20that%20or%20do%20you%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20better%20off%20just%20ignored%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20he%20used%20to%20be%20very%20polite%20when%20he%20came%20to%20the%20RBI%20and%20met%20me%20on%20some%20issue%20or%20the%20other.%20Let%20me%20not%20get%20into%20the%20language%20of%20the%20street%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20dignified.%20But%20I%20mean%20when%20people%20couch%20it%20with%20that%2C%20it%20makes%20debate%20much%20harder.%20Hopefully%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20both%20on%20the%20same%20side%20%E2%80%93%20we%20want%20jobs%20for%20India.%20What%20we%E2%80%99re%20disputing%20is%20whether%20the%20jobs%20will%20come%20through%20the%20scheme%20the%20government%20is%20suggesting.%20I%20really%20hope%20it%20will%2C%20but%20I%20would%20want%20the%20government%20to%20continuously%20evaluate%2C%20in%20an%20independent%20way%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20doing%20that%20and%20given%20that%20the%20data%20are%20so%20hard%20to%20get%2C%20and%20given%20even%20then%20it%20can%20be%20massaged%20and%20manipulated%2C%20you%20really%20need%20an%20independent%20evaluation%20agency%20to%20look%20at%20this%20to%20get%20the%20data%20to%20us.%20And%20why%20I%20say%20this%20is%20because%20we%E2%80%99re%20expanding%20the%20scheme%20left%20right%20and%20centre%2C%20and%20we%20have%20to%20ask%20is%20this%20really%20the%20way%20to%20go%2C%20is%20the%20government%20actually%20better%20off%3F%20Because%20the%20country%20needs%20jobs%2C%20there%20are%20no%20two%20questions%20about%20it.%20How%20we%20produce%20those%20jobs%2C%20that%20to%20my%20mind%20is%20a%20central%20question%2C%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20hear%20that%20addressed%20so%20far.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20put%20you%20what%20someone%20said%20about%20the%20personal%20attack%20on%20you%20made%20by%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar.%20This%20person%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPoliticians%20only%20resort%20to%20vituperative%20language%20when%20actually%20they%20realise%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20got%20a%20good%20case%20to%20make.%20They%20buttress%20the%20bankruptcy%20of%20their%20arguments%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20using%20his%20language%20against%20him%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cby%20using%20the%20vituperative%20personal%20language%20instead.%E2%80%9D%20So%20does%20his%20personal%20critique%20of%20you%20suggest%20that%20actually%2C%20he%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20got%20good%20arguments%20to%20make%20which%20is%20why%20he%E2%80%99s%20speaking%20in%20these%20terms%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20would%20say%20after%20a%20six-page%20note%20%E2%80%93%20which%20again%20I%20think%20is%20commendable%20that%20he%20took%20the%20time%20to%20write%20it%20%E2%80%93%20he%20basically%20agrees%20with%20the%20argument%3A%20it%E2%80%99s%20just%20assembly.%20And%20where%20he%20says%20%E2%80%98lies%2C%20lies%2C%20lies%2C%E2%80%99%20we%20said%2040%25%20to%2080%25%2C%20he%20says%2065%25.%20Well%20if%20that%E2%80%99s%20lies%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20happy%20to%20live%20with%20those%20lies%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20part%20of%20the%20academic%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20he%20agrees%20with%20everything%20we%20say.%20The%20difference%20is%20he%20thinks%20good%20stuff%20is%20going%20to%20come%20in%20the%20future.%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20quite%20skeptical%20about%20that%2C%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20come.%20And%20if%20as%20he%20says%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20at%20this%20since%202014%2C%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20come%20for%20nine%20years.%20You%20remember%20%5BAlbert%5D%20Einstein%E2%80%99s%20definition%20of%20insanity%3A%20doing%20the%20same%20thing%20and%20expecting%20a%20different%20result.%20%5B%3Cstrong%3EEditor%E2%80%99s%20note%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20quote%20is%20often%20attributed%20to%20Einstein%2C%20but%20there%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Fnews%2Fhere-are-6-things-albert-einstein-never-said%5C%22%3Eno%20evidence%20he%20said%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%5D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20I%20would%20hope%20this%20works%20becau