%20situation%3A%20expert%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20jets%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da1edd5e5d5a00195d4371%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMembers%20of%20the%20Russian%20Air%20Force%20perform%20with%20their%20Su-27%20type%20aircraft%20during%20the%20International%20Air%20Show%20at%20the%20Hungarian%20Air%20Force%20base%20in%20Kecskemet%2C%20southern%20Hungary%2C%20on%20August%203%2C%202013.%3Cp%3EATTILA%20KISBENEDEK%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAn%20expert%20said%20the%20Russian%20air%20force%20is%20being%20depleted%20through%20overuse%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20arrival%20of%20Ukraine's%20F-16s%20could%20worsen%20the%20problem%2C%20wrote%20Rand's%20Michael%20Bohnert.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUkraine%20says%20it%20urgently%20needs%20F-16s%20to%20reduce%20Russia's%20air%20dominance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20fighter%20planes%20are%20malfunctioning%20because%20of%20overuse%2C%20handing%20Ukraine%20a%20potential%20advantage%20in%20its%20air%20battles%20against%20the%20Russian%20air%20force%2C%20an%20expert%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20article%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensenews.com%2Fopinion%2F2023%2F08%2F14%2Fhow-f-16s-for-ukraine-could-harm-russia-without-taking-a-single-shot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20Defense%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Michael%20Bohnert%2C%20an%20engineering%20expert%20at%20the%20Rand%20Corporation%20think%20tank%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensenews.com%2Fopinion%2F2023%2F08%2F14%2Fhow-f-16s-for-ukraine-could-harm-russia-without-taking-a-single-shot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20Russia's%20warplanes%20are%20running%20out%20of%20%26quot%3Baircraft%20life%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOveruse%20of%20these%20aircraft%20is%20also%20costing%20Russia%20as%20the%20war%20drags%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20saying%20that%20by%20his%20calculations%20as%20many%20as%2057%20Russian%20planes%2C%20many%20repurposed%20Soviet-era%20machines%2C%20may%20have%20been%20lost%20because%20they%20broke%20down%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20in%20addition%20to%20UK%20intelligence%20figures%2C%20which%20suggest%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1626117344186576896%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0around%20130%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20estimated%20900%20planes%20in%20Russia's%20air%20force%20deployed%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20crashed%20or%20been%20shot%20down%20during%20the%20war.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20writes%20that%20because%20many%20of%20the%20aircraft%20are%20reaching%20the%20limit%20of%20their%203%2C000%20hours%20of%20flight%20time%2C%20the%20problem%20could%20worsen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20up%20for%20it%2C%20they'll%20have%20to%20procure%20more%20aircraft%2C%20increase%20maintenance%2C%20reduce%20operations%2C%20or%20accept%20a%20smaller%20force%20%E2%80%94%20or%20some%20combination%20of%20those%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20delivery%20of%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20to%20Ukraine%20by%20its%20Western%20allies%2C%20which%20has%20been%20delayed%20by%20bureaucracy%2C%20could%20damage%20Russia's%20air%20force%20even%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20VKS%20%5BRussian%20air%20force%5D%20devotes%20a%20greater%20share%20of%20its%20dwindling%20force%20to%20countering%20those%2C%20it%20will%20have%20fewer%20aircraft%20left%20to%20support%20Russian%20ground%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BVKS%20fighters%20in%20the%20sky%20will%20also%20be%20less%20capable%2C%20stemming%20from%20two%20years%20of%20overuse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20experts%20share%20Bohnert's%20conclusions.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fpublications%2Fthe-military-balance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBritish%20think%20tank%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20a%20report%20said%20that%20Russia%20retained%20the%20capacity%20to%20rapidly%20add%20to%20its%20aircraft%20supplies%20from%20its%20aeronautical%20factories%2C%20potentially%20meaning%20old%20aircraft%20can%20be%20quickly%20replaced%2C%20and%20its%20overall%20strength%20in%20the%20air%20had%20not%20significantly%20diminished.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20weeks%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20some%20analysts%20believed%20that%20Russia%20would%20be%20able%20to%20establish%20rapid%20control%20of%20Ukrainian%20air%20space%2C%20with%20its%20air%20force%20more%20sophisticated%20than%20and%20bigger%20than%20Ukraine's.%20But%20effective%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses%20meant%20that%20Russia%20was%20unable%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20seeks%20to%20retake%20territory%20from%20Russia%20in%20its%20counteroffensive%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20requesting%20F-16s%20from%20its%20Western%20allies%20that%20it%20says%20would%20help%20tip%20the%20air%20battle%20in%20its%20favor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-quickly-depleting-fleet-warplanes-overuse-expert-ukraine-f16-worsen-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692021223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da1ee85e5d5a00195d4383%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-quickly-depleting-fleet-warplanes-overuse-expert-ukraine-f16-worsen-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia's%20air%20force%20is%20running%20into%20problems%20due%20to%20aging%20aircraft%20as%20its%20war%20with%20Ukrain